<plot>A short film about the passage of time-and the rites of passage On one fateful day, five characters' tensions clash as they await major life events... the death of a family member, the blossoming of a young romance, the return of a husband. "Life At Bay" explores the notion of living in the moment, and the drifting feeling of being in limbo even while there is so much going on.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?335701</url></doc>
